  "text": "Found 7 deprecated classes in Apache Flink's flink-streaming-java/src/main/java directory. These deprecated DataStream API classes are scheduled for removal:\n\n1. **TextInputFormat** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/legacy/io/TextInputFormat.java) - An I/O format class for reading text files. Marked @Deprecated with recommendation to use FLIP-27 FileSource and Sink-V2 FlinkSink instead.\n\n2. **TextOutputFormat** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/legacy/io/TextOutputFormat.java) - An I/O format class for writing text files. Marked @Deprecated with recommendation to use FLIP-27 FileSource and Sink-V2 FlinkSink instead.\n\n3. **DiscardingSink** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/functions/sink/legacy/DiscardingSink.java) - A sink function that ignores all elements. Marked @Deprecated with recommendation to use org.apache.flink.streaming.api.functions.sink.v2.DiscardingSink instead.\n\n4. **TwoPhaseCommitSinkFunction** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/functions/sink/legacy/TwoPhaseCommitSinkFunction.java) - A base class for sink functions implementing exactly-once semantics via two-phase commit. Marked @Deprecated with recommendation to use org.apache.flink.api.connector.sink2.Sink interface instead.\n\n5. **DataGeneratorSource** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/functions/source/datagen/DataGeneratorSource.java) - A source function for generating test data. Marked @Deprecated with recommendation to use org.apache.flink.connector.datagen.source.DataGeneratorSource instead.\n\n6. **AscendingTimestampExtractor** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/functions/timestamps/AscendingTimestampExtractor.java) - A timestamp extractor and watermark generator for monotonously ascending timestamps. Marked @Deprecated @PublicEvolving with no specific replacement mentioned in the javadoc.\n\n7. **StreamingFileSink** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/functions/sink/filesystem/legacy/StreamingFileSink.java) - A sink that writes to files within buckets with exactly-once semantics. Marked @Deprecated with recommendation to use org.apache.flink.connector.file.sink.FileSink instead.\n\nThese classes are primarily deprecated source functions, sink functions, timestamp extractors, and I/O format classes from the DataStream API that have been superseded by newer implementations in the connector modules or newer versions of the API."
}

